Ford Go Bike Trip DATA¶

Overview¶

in this Analysis i want to see what is the common relation of the users characterstic and the effect on the trips duration they made i focused on top 12 trips made¶

Data overlook¶

the data consist from trip trip info (start and end station and time) and user info (gender and birthyear and type)¶

plot 4¶

now let`s see the correlation again between age and duration for each of our top 12 trip¶

In [19]:
#remove outliere from our groph and set limit to 50
h=sb.FacetGrid(data=top_frame,col='the_trip_rank',col_wrap=3,legend_out=True)
h.map(sb.regplot,'age','duration_in_min',line_kws={'color':'r'},scatter_kws={'alpha':.3})
plt.ylim((0,50))
plt.xlim(10,60)
h.fig.subplots_adjust(top=0.9)
h.fig.suptitle('relation between age and duration in min for top 12 trips');

we can see that the correlation still weak but the range of our customer is limited at top 8 and top 10 trips¶
